      "span_text": "It has long been known that lung pathology can directly lead to cardiac disease, such as in cor pulmonale, in which right-sided heart failure is a result of increased pulmonary arterial pressure; this increase in pressure may be caused by a panoply of diseases, including pulmonary fibrosis and COPD. [CITATION_1]"
